  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AL-02 sensitivity gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across all five flow-speed operating points; a screening sensitivity study was conducted during model development to rank input parameters by their contribution to output variance — however that study is described only in the supporting technical report and has not been encoded as a structured hasSensitivityAnalysis link in this package. All thirteen credibility factors are assessed; seven achieve their required gradation and six remain one gradation below the required level. Decision: Accepted with conditions pending resolution of outstanding credibility gaps.",
