      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Documented simulation setup checklist reviewed by a second analyst; boundary condition inputs cross-checked against experimental records.",
      "rationale": "Simulation setup was performed by a single analyst without independent cross-check. Boundary conditions were documented but not formally reviewed against experimental records by a second party. Achieved gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection justified by comparison of at least two RANS closures against experimental velocity data; hemolysis power-law exponents sourced from peer-reviewed literature with uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega and realizable k-epsilon were compared; SST k-omega selected based on better near-wall velocity agreement. Hemolysis power-law exponents taken from Giersiepen et al. without propagated uncertainty bounds. Achieved gradation 3. Note: the UQ study propagates inlet boundary condition uncertainty and geometric tolerance uncertainty through the hemolysis model using Monte Carlo sampling (10 000 draws per operating point); a screening sensitivity study described in the technical report identified inlet flow rate and impeller tip clearance as the dominant variance contributors, but this study has not been encoded as a structured sensitivity analysis record in the present package.",
      "uqNote": "Monte Carlo UQ performed; screening sensitivity study referenced in technical report but not linked as structured hasSensitivityAnalysis record."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All uncertain model inputs characterized with probability distributions derived from measurement data or literature; distributions propagated through model via Monte Carlo UQ.",
      "rationale": "Inlet flow rate, rotational speed, fluid viscosity, and impeller tip clearance were assigned probability distributions based on manufacturing tolerances and measurement uncertainty. Monte Carlo UQ with 10 000 samples per operating point was executed. Distribution parameters for fluid viscosity relied on a single literature source rather than device-specific measurements. Achieved gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "At least three independent experimental replicates per operating point; sample-to-sample variability reported.",
      "rationale": "Two independent replicates were performed at each of four operating points; only one replicate available at the fifth (extrapolated) operating point. Sample-to-sample variability reported for the four replicated points. Achieved gradation 2."
    },
